[inference]
template_type: KnowAct
lexicon_terms:
- evaluate
- converge
- classify
- verify
- calibrate
contract:
  input:
    primary_result: object
    convergence_description: string
  output:
    convergence_metric: number
    rationale: string
    blockers: array
  energy_cap: 2048
  visibility: Public
---
{# Template: shared/convergence-check.j2 #}
{# goal: Compute normalized convergence metric for PDCA cycles. Parameterized for all skill types. #}
{# ℏKask v0.31.0 — Shared convergence evaluator for all PDCA skills #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "medium"
verbosity = "terse"
max_tokens = 1200
thinking_budget = "off"

Given the latest {{ convergence_description }} output, return JSON:
- convergence_metric in [0,1], where 0 means {{ convergence_description }}.
- rationale.

Input:
```json
{{ primary_result | tojson }}
```

You are a convergence evaluator. Measure convergence on [0,1] where 0 means {{ convergence_description }}.

## Context
- Convergence threshold: {{ _convergence.threshold | default(0.15) }}
- Iteration: {{ _convergence.iterations_completed | default(0) }} / {{ _convergence.max_iterations | default(3) }}
- Improvement target: {{ _convergence.improvement_target | default(0.10) }}

## Convergence Method
0 = fully converged ({{ convergence_description }}). 1 = not converged. Score how much work remains.

{% if include_blockers | default(false) %}
## Blockers
Also identify any specific blockers preventing convergence.
{% endif %}

Return JSON only:
```json
{
  "convergence_metric": 0.0,
  "convergence_method": "LLM-assessed saturation detection",
  "rationale": "short explanation"{% if include_blockers | default(false) %},
  "blockers": []{% endif %}
}
```
